"title": "6251: temptation, resisting",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6251: temptation, resisting",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Being tempted is not in itself a sin. Sin arises when believers give in to temptation. Scripture urges believers to resist temptation, and gives them encouragement to face it.</p>\n<h2>Encouragement to those facing temptation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:12\">JAS 1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:37\">ROM 8:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:18\">HEB 2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15-Heb4:16\">HEB 4:15–4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:2-Jas1:3\">JAS 1:2–1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:4\">1JN 4:4</a></p>\n<h2>Finding in God and his word resources to overcome temptation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:32\">DAN 11:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:1-Prov2:2\">PRO 2:1–2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:12-Prov2:15\">PRO 2:12–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:13\">MAT 6:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:4\">LUK 11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:11-1Tim6:12\">1TI 6:11–6:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:7\">JAS 4:7</a></p>\n<h2>Practical suggestions for overcoming temptation</h2>\n<h3>Overcoming temptation through prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:41\">MAT 26:41</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:38\">MRK 14:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:40\">LUK 22:40</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:8-Matt18:9\">MAT 18:8–18:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:5\">1CO 7:5</a></p>\n<h3>Overcoming temptation through personal discipline</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:4\">HEB 12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:7\">HEB 12:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:17\">2PE 3:17</a></p>\n<h2>Encouragements to resist temptation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:1\">GAL 6:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:22\">1TH 5:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:10-Prov1:15\">PRO 1:10–1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:12-Rom6:14\">ROM 6:12–6:14</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of those who did not give in to temptation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:22\">JOB 1:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:7-Gen39:10\">GEN 39:7–39:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:10\">JOB 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:5-Jer35:6\">JER 35:5–35:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:8\">DAN 1:8</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ resisted temptation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:4\">MAT 4:4</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:4\">LUK 4:4</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:7\">MAT 4:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:12\">LUK 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:10\">MAT 4:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:8\">LUK 4:8</a></p>",
